  "doc_id": "61424",
  "text": "Here, we show how phylogenetic uncertainty can be incorporated in many of the models that biologists commonly employ. BUGS code for each model is provided in an Additional file 1. With some minor changes, these scripts can also be run using the program JAGS [CITATION_1] . We explore the behaviour of the models using simulated data sets, and illustrate their application to two real data sets of plant traits. Finally, we discuss the performance and relevance of this approach, and possibilities for extensions.",
